Nsbssg21
S'You are standing shin-deep in an underground river that flows through a tunnel from the west to the east. To the west a soft, gentle light filters down from a hole in the ceiling, whereas to the east is nothing but the pitch-blackness of an enternal subterraignian night.'
sg22
S'You would not be able to travel any further East away from the light spiling down from the hole in the ceiling to the West without anything but the un-aided naked eye.'
sbsI129
