S"What appeared to be a small dugout from the path below you actually turns out to be a carefully carved cave leading into the heart of the volcano. Heat from the molten lava within the depts of the volcano rolls out across your face, a distinctly different sensation from the cool ocean breeze blowing across your back. The walls of the cave are perfectly smooth, and the shape of the cave has been prefectly rounded. The cave continues to the north, where a small ledge juts out from the volcano's interior wall."
sg22
S"You can walk North towards the heart of the fiery volcano, or climb back Down to the path that winds around it's southern face."
