S'You now standing knee-deep in an underground river that flows through an underground tunnel. The air smells strongly of dank rock and saltwater. A gentle light drifts down from the end of a long circular shaft in the ceiling of the tunnel. The light is sufficient for you to see around you, but only dim enough to permit black and white night vision. Just below the surface of the water you can see many flat round objects that are made out of a metal that has rusted away to nothing but delicate wafers. If they were once coins they are most certainly useless now, as they completely flake apart whenever you try to pick one up for a closer examination.'
sg22
S"You may travel East or West through the tunnel, though you can't see very far in either direction because the light from above doesn't help to illuminate very far to either side of you. The walls of the shaft leading Up through the ceiling are too slick for you climb up with your bare hands."
