S"You are standing ankle-deep in a river that flows from the west to the east through an underground tunnel. The ceiling and floor of the underground tunnel declines below the waterline to the east. You would have to be very confident in your ability to hold your breath if you wanted to follow the river in that direction, since you would have to be swimming underwater. You certainly wouldn't want to risk being trapped underground, in a water-filled tunnel, struggling against the current trying to find the surface! To the west of you the river is bathed in complete darkness."
sg22
S'You are in a very precarious situation, as you would need light to be able to move to the West, and you would have to hold your breath for an unknown period of time if you wanted to swim Down under the water.'
