S'You are now facing the southern side of a long wall that divides the western half of the island. This particular section of the wall has begun to fall into disrepare, after what appears to be many years of neglect. Some of the bricks have become somewhat loose, and you feel a little wary of anything that might fall from above, causing you to glance up towards the top of the wall repeatedly. To the west of you the wall twists to the south and forms a staircase that leads into the northern face of a small volcano. To the east the ground drops off sharply, and nothing but weeds and thorned bushes cover the land.'
sg22
S'Between the wall in front of you and the poor terraign to the east, you may only return South, to the bottom of the the twisting staircase.'
