S"This end of the large underground room is mainly taken up by a large stone statue of a human skeleton that is bound to an ornate alter of some sort. The statue is placed upright against the wall of the room, giving the impression that you were floating in space above the remains of the victim's body. Apparently this room was once used for some form of human sacrifice. At the northeastern end of this room lies a smaller tunnel which appears to have been closed off by the building of a stone wall."
sg22
