S'You are standing on the northeastern side of a low hill that gently slopes its way down to a green pasture. There are two long walls running east-west and north-south across the top of the hill. You are standing in front of a large metal gate that has been built into the wall that runs north-south across the hill. There is an enormous and elaborately-decorated lock with a large keyhole centered in the middle of the gate. You can see a cobblestone path leading towards the immense ruins of a once great manor on the other side of the gate.'
sg22
S'You can go SouthWest along the top of the hill, or East through the gate, if it is open.'
