S"You have removed the cave-in left behind in the tunnel to the south of you, and followed it into an enormous underground cavern, something that presents a spectacle unlike anything that you've ever seen before. \012\012\011The tunnel leads out onto a ledge that reaches halfway out into the cavern. There are various holes far above your head in the stone ceiling of the cavern, which filter in shafts of light that fall at obscure angles onto various locations throughout the entire area.\012\012\011The far wall of the cavern reaches down from the top of the ceiling to far beyond your range of vision, down into the depths below. There is a steady stream of water cascading down the far wall, and in certain areas small mechanisms which resemble the balances of a scale capture some of the streams running down the rockface into small cups, which cause the opposite sides of the balance to rise and pour water into other devices. The reaction is that when water runs down a certain area of the wall, a chain reaction between the devices is enacted in one direction, and then as the water spills out from the cups, a new chain reaction develops across another portion of the large chamber.\012\012\011The air is fill with the sound of gushing water, and the rapid clicking of many of these devices, as their cups fill and the balances switch to the other side. In a few places, some sort of crystal is placed upon the top of the balance. If the water falls in a particular pattern, the crystal will cross into the path of a beam of light that falls from the ceiling above, causing new rays of light to refract in other directions, sometimes touching other scales, and sometimes refracting off stationary crystals imbeded directly into the various walls of the cavern. Such activities continue all the way down the far cavern wall, for as far as your eye can  see.\012\012\011Across the abyss below you lies another platform to the west. On this ledge a series of gears and levers are imbeded into the rock, perhaps to control the flow of the water above, and therefore the visual patterns created by the balances and beams of light.\012\012\011The overall effect of this grandeous machincal process quickly begins to overwhelm you senses with a sense of awe and appreciation for the machine's beauty.\012\012\011At the end of the platform on which you are standing are four different pedestools, each with a consistent height approximately equal to the level of your shoulders. There is a beam of light falling from the ceiling above that crosses just above the top of each of these pedestools, at varying angles. Each of the pedestools is of a slightly differnt hue, one white, one black, one blue, and one red."
sg22
S'You may only return North, to the area where the cave-in took place.'
