S'This branch of the underground tunnel system is somewhat wider than the tunnel the southwest, allowing you just enough room to stand up fully erect. The walls of the this tunnel are far more solid as well. On the eastern wall of this particular section a large, flat, stone surface has been inlade. On the surface of the stone are various markings and pictures of human-shaped creatures involved in what appears to be a ritual of some sort, but that is about all that you can make out for certain. The tunnel continues to the north and to the south, and connects with a smaller tunnel system to the southwest.'
sg22
S'You can either follow the Northern, Southern, or SouthWestern tunnels.'
