S'As you continue to crawl through the tunnel, you pause for a moment to take a closer look at the walls of this passageway. The entire tunnel system is dimly lit, though there is no single source of origin for the light. Examinging the soil in detail, you can see what appears to be millions of tiny phosphorus fungi that appear to glow with a yellowish inner light. This is very fortunate for you, as you would otherwise be totally unable to find your way around by using your naked eyes alone. Taking another moment to better orient yourself, you see that the underground tunnel system forks here in three directions.'
sg22
S'One passage continues North and heads at a angle slightly sloping downward angle, another goes NorthEast, and the last passage continues to the South.'
